<h3 id=3D"TheXmlTextFieldType-ForXHTMLInput"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,=
0);">For XHTML Input</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">The eZ XML output use &lt;strong&gt; =
and &lt;em&gt; by default, respecting the semantic XHTML notation.<br></spa=
n></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro has-no-icon confluence-informati=
on-macro-information">
<p class=3D"title">Learn more about &lt;strong&gt;, &lt;b&gt;, &lt;em&gt;, =
&lt;i&gt;</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/forums/exponential-5-platform/strong-vs-b-=
and-em-vs-i" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Read the share.ez.no =
forum about our choice of semantic tags with eZ XML</a></li>
<li>Learn more <a href=3D"http://html5doctor.com/i-b-em-strong-element/" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">about the semantic tags vs the prese=
ntational tags.</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><br></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"TheXmlTextFieldType-InputobjectAPI"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0=
,0);">Input object API</span></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><code><strong>Input</strong></code> o=
bject is intended as a vector for different input formats. It should accept=
 input value in a foreign format and convert it to the FieldType's internal=
 format.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">It should implement abstract&nbsp;</s=
pan><strong><code>eZ\Publish\Core\FieldType\XmlText\Input</code></strong> c=
lass, which defines only one method:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Method</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><pre><span>getInternalRepresentation</span></pre=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The method should return the input value in the =
internal format.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">At the moment there is only one imple=
mentation of the <strong><code>Input</code></strong></span><span style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(0,0,0);">&nbsp;class, </span><strong><code style=3D"line-height: =
1.4285715;">eZ\Publish\Core\FieldType\XmlText\Input\EzXml</code></strong><s=
pan style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">, which accepts input value in the interna=
l format, and therefore only performs validation of the input value.</span>=
</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>Example of using the Input object</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: true; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size:=
12px;">...
&nbsp;
use eZ\Publish\Core\FieldType\XmlText\Input\EzXml as EzXmlInput;

...

$contentService =3D $repository-&gt;getContentService();
$contentTypeService =3D $repository-&gt;getContentTypeService();
&nbsp;
$contentType =3D $contentTypeService-&gt;loadContentTypeByIdentifier( "arti=
cle" );
$contentCreateStruct =3D $contentService-&gt;newContentCreateStruct( $conte=
ntType, "eng-GB" );

$inputString =3D &lt;&lt;&lt;EZXML
&lt;?xml version=3D"1.0" encoding=3D"utf-8"?&gt;
&lt;section
=09xmlns:custom=3D"http://ez.no/namespaces/exponential3/custom/"
=09xmlns:image=3D"http://ez.no/namespaces/exponential3/image/"
=09xmlns:xhtml=3D"http://ez.no/namespaces/exponential3/xhtml/"&gt;
    &lt;paragraph&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/paragraph&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
EZXML;
&nbsp;
$ezxmlInput =3D new EzXmlInput( $inputString );

$contentCreateStruct-&gt;setField( "description", $ezxmlInput );
&nbsp;
...</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"TheXmlTextFieldType-ValueobjectAPI"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0=
,0);">Value object API</span></h2>
<p><strong><code>eZ\Publish\Core\FieldType\XmlText\Value</code></strong>&nb=
sp;offers following properties:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
